    "description": {
      "value": "<p>On your turn, when you score a Critical Hit or reduce a creature to 0 hit points, you can immediately attempt to hinder other threats around you. A number of creatures of your choice within 10 feet of you or the target equal to your Proficiency Bonus must make a Charisma saving throw (DC 8 plus your Proficiency Bonus plus the ability modifier used) or become hindered until the end of their next turn. While hindered a creature cannot take Reactions and can only take an action or a Bonus Action, not both. You may only impose the saving throw from Thwart once per turn on a creature.</p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"secret-NbyZUqEjNogjvGR3\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>By default this feat uses Strength for the saving throw DC, if you wish to use a different ability modifier instead, update this feat after it has been added to your character sheet.</p></section>",
